g.text: Vertical addition is a standard method for adding multi-digit numbers by aligning digits in columns.

ul.li: Arrange numbers vertically, aligning digits by place value.
Draw a horizontal line below the bottom addend.
Add digits column by column, starting from the rightmost column (ones place).
If the sum of a column is ≤ 9, write the sum below the line.
If the sum is > 9, write the rightmost digit and carry over the leftmost digit(s) to the next column.
Vertical addition aligns digits by place value for accurate calculation.
Start adding from the rightmost column (ones place).
Carry over when the sum of a column exceeds 9.
